        <div class="section-eyebrow">My Background</div>
        <h2>15+ years of building learning that <em>sticks.</em></h2>
        <p class="body-text">I started my career as a high school teacher, teaching AP Psychology, AP World History, Geography, and U.S. History. I loved the classroom, but I was equally fascinated by the design behind it: why some lessons landed and others didn't, why some assessments revealed real understanding while others just measured memorization.</p>
        <p class="body-text">That curiosity led me into online teaching and learning. I designed and taught an OER-based Introduction to Psychology course for the Utah Education Network, then joined Lumen Learning in 2014 — where what started as course design gradually became something bigger: owning and running a full catalog of high-enrollment digital courseware across Psychology, Sociology, Economics, History, and more. That means defining course strategy, hiring and directing subject matter experts, managing production across multiple concurrent projects, and using learner engagement data to figure out what's working and what needs to change.</p>
        <p class="body-text">In 2024, I returned to the classroom as an Adjunct Professor of Psychology at Davidson College, designing and delivering a flipped, application-based Intro Psych course. Teaching my own product in a live environment was one of the most valuable things I've ever done as a designer. I am still passionate about teaching, presenting, and creating.</p>
        <p class="body-text">Most recently, I've been deep in experiments with Claude Code and AI agents. When I'm not at my computer, you can find me on a soccer field or back in a school, coaching my kids' sporting teams and improv classes. I love spending time with my family and our beloved Aussiedoodle, Cosmo. In my free time I'm usually attending basketball games, watching musicals, running, baking sourdough bread and cookies, hiking, or sneaking off to Europe to practice my Deutsch.</p>
      </div>
